		analysis: "Confirmation fatigue: 200 confirmations/day = muscle memory 'always click Confirm.' Modal becomes invisible — user doesn't read. When genuinely dangerous action appears (delete fornecedor): user auto-confirms because previous 199 confirmations trained 'always Confirm.' Confirmation designed to prevent error CAUSED the error. Root cause: every action has same protection level regardless of consequence."
		recommendation: "(1) Classify all actions by severity: **No confirmation (immediate + undo toast):** change sort, toggle sidebar, change filter, close panel, change display preference, toggle notification. Total: ~150/day. Now: zero friction. Undo toast for 5 seconds if accidentally toggled. **Inline confirmation (lightweight, at point of action):** reject operation (medium, reversible — can re-submit), archive fornecedor, change threshold. Inline: 'Rejeitar? [Sim] [Cancelar]' at row level. Total: ~10/day. **Modal confirmation (explicit, with impact):** approve operation (financial), batch approve, change access permissions. Modal: action description + impact metrics + deliberate button. Total: ~15/day. **Typed confirmation (maximum friction):** delete fornecedor permanently, remove user. Type entity name to proceed. Total: <1/day. (2) Result: from 200 modals/day to: 0 modals for routine + 10 inline for medium + 15 modals for high + <1 typed for critical = ~25 total friction points. 87% reduction in friction. (3) The 25 remaining confirmations MATTER: user reads modal because it only appears for consequential actions. Delete fornecedor: typed confirmation requires reading name and typing it — cannot auto-confirm. (4) Implement undo for demoted actions: filter change: instant + undo. Sort change: instant + undo. Close panel: instant + reopen shortcut. Toggle: instant + undo toast. (5) Communicate change to users: 'atualizamos confirmações para serem proporcionais à importância da ação. Ações rotineiras não pedem confirmação (têm desfazer). Ações financeiras mantêm confirmação detalhada.' (6) Monitor: after change, track: accidental action rate. If accidental deletes increase (unlikely with typed confirmation): re-evaluate. If accidental filter changes increase: undo window sufficient? Adjust undo window (5s → 10s) if needed."
