limitations: [
	{
		description: "Keyboard shortcuts require learning investment and are invisible to novice users."
		alternative: "Progressive accelerators: buttons for everyone (tier 1), tooltips show shortcuts (tier 2, discoverable), command palette for experts (tier 3). Document all shortcuts in accessible location ('?' key). Never remove button in favor of shortcut — shortcut supplements, doesn't replace."
		rationale: "Shortcuts are acceleration, not replacement. Expert discovers gradually. Novice always has buttons."
	},
	{
		description: "Smart defaults that are wrong are worse than no defaults — user trusts default and submits incorrect data (e.g., wrong bank account for payment)."
		alternative: "Default from user's own data (last used, profile). Never default financial amounts (risk of wrong number). Never default recipient for payment (wrong recipient = lost money). Default only when: source is reliable (user's own profile, extracted from uploaded document) AND consequence of wrong default is low or caught by validation."
		rationale: "Default what's safe to default. Review: which defaults, if wrong, cause financial loss? Those: don't default."
	},
	{
		description: "Batch operations on financial actions carry aggregate risk — approving 50 operations in one click commits R$1.2M."
		alternative: "Batch confirmation always shows: count + total amount + breakdown. Maximum batch size limit (configurable). For very large batches (>100 or >R$1M): additional confirmation tier (typed confirmation or two-person approval). Audit log: who batch-approved, when, what."
		rationale: "Batch efficiency must not compromise financial safety. Aggregate impact visibility + audit trail = responsible batch."
	},
	{
		description: "Command palette requires significant implementation effort (search index, fuzzy matching, action integration) and may be underutilized if user base is small."
		alternative: "Prioritize: shortcuts first (lower effort, immediate benefit for known actions). Command palette: implement when app has >20 distinct actions and >5 active power users. Simpler alternative: global search (entities only, no actions) as stepping stone."
		rationale: "Command palette is high-value for experts at scale. For early-stage: shortcuts + global search covers 80% of benefit at 30% of effort."
	},
	{
		description: "Inline editing in tables may cause accidental modifications — user clicks cell intending to select row but triggers edit mode."
		alternative: "Explicit edit trigger: double-click to edit (not single-click). Or: edit icon appears on hover, click icon to enter edit mode. Single-click = select row. Double-click = edit cell. Clear separation between selection and editing."
		rationale: "Accidental edit in financial table has consequence. Edit trigger must be deliberate (double-click or explicit icon), not accidental (single-click that was meant to select)."
	},
]

rationale: "Ferramentas profissionais B2B são usadas horas por dia, e cada interação ineficiente multiplica por volume de uso. Na Mesh com construtoras aprovando 20 operações/dia, FIDC analisando 100 operações/dia, e fornecedores submetendo antecipações semanalmente, esta lens operacionaliza: forms com smart defaults e inline validation que reduzem input de 3 minutos para 30 segundos (Wroblewski 2008, smart defaults 2023+, inline validation 2022+, progressive complexity 2024+), feedback com skeleton e progressive loading que otimiza perceived speed (Nielsen 1994, Miller 1968, optimistic UI 2023+, skeleton Wroblewski 2013, progressive loading 2024+), keyboard shortcuts e command palette que aceleram experts (Fitts' Law 1954, progressive accelerators 2023+, command palette 2022+), confirmação proporcional à consequência que previne confirmation fatigue (action severity 2023+, undo as safety net 2024+), batch operations com persistent selection que transformam 30 minutos em 90 segundos (persistent selection 2024+, selection persistence 2023+), interaction states consistentes que constroem predictability (state consistency 2024+), inline editing que elimina context switches para edits frequentes (click-to-edit 2023+, autosave 2024+), e skeleton/progressive loading que otimiza percepção de velocidade (Wroblewski 2013, progressive 2024+). Universal para qualquer B2B tool onde eficiência de interação é multiplicada por volume de uso diário."

}
